race.description: Bet365 Same Race Multi Maiden Plate
race.comment: BURLEIGH (1) has filled a minor placing at both runs this time in work and is ready to break through for the premiership yard. He was a tad disappointing at Ararat last time, backed off the map, and drops back to a shorter sprint today off a freshen. Wary of MY CHERIE AMOR (9) on debut for a top metro stable. She's looked the goods at the Flemington jumpouts and the blinkers are applied, signalling intent. She's likely to ride the speed and give a big sight in country grade. BELLA ANGELICA (6) has an awkward barrier but worked into a place at Mt Gambier over a short course and will be better again over the longer sprint. She just missed as favourite at Warrnambool on debut and is looking to recapture that form. DYNAMITE DANCER (3) placed on the heavy at Warrnambool on debut well-supported. Has been given 40 days away and is back with Yendall booked. Maps well and quick improvement is likely. HELLISH LEE (8) had excuses last time off a tidy placing at Dunkeld on debut.
